An acute isosceles triangle, $ABC$, is inscribed in a circle.  Through $B$ and $C$, tangents to the circle are drawn, meeting at point $D$.  If $\angle ABC = \angle ACB = 2 \angle D$ and $\angle BAC = k \pi$ in radians, then find $k$.

[asy]
